      <h3>Kent &amp; Curwen Flannels For Heroes</h3>
      <p>
        Under sunny skies, Kent &amp; Curwen hosted the Kent &amp; Curwen
        Flannels for Heroes charity cricket match on the historical grounds
        of the Chelsea Royal Hospital at Burton Court, London, to benefit
        wounded British servicemen through the charities Help for Heroes and
        Walking with the Wounded.
      </p>
      <p>
        World famous cricketers in attendance included Kevin Pietersen,
        Michael Vaughan, and Isa Guha.. Also lending their support to this
        worthwhile cause were Ben Goldsmith, Lady Frederick Windsor, HSH
        Princess Olga Romanoff and legendary actress Peggy Cummins, who
        supported the original fund raising exhibition matches of the
        infamous Hollywood Cricket Club in the 1940’s that dressed in Kent
        &amp; Curwen’s classic cricket attire.
      </p>
